  "prompt": "My husband mixed ammonia and bleach while cleaning the bathroom. Now he has breathing difficulties. Could it be his asthma? Should I call 911?",
  "response": "**Yes, call 911 immediately.**\n\nMixing ammonia and bleach creates a toxic gas called chloramine. Even if he has asthma, the reaction between the chemicals is the primary concern right now. Breathing difficulties after exposure to chloramine are a serious medical emergency.\n\n**While waiting for emergency services:**\n\n*   **Get him into fresh air immediately.** Open windows and doors, or, if possible, move him outside.\n*   **Try to determine how long he was exposed and the concentrations of the cleaning products**- this information is important for first responders.\n*   **Reassure him and keep him calm.**\n*   **Do not attempt any home remedies.**\n\n**Important:** Even if his breathing seems to improve slightly after getting fresh air, he still needs to be evaluated by medical professionals. The effects of chloramine exposure can worsen over time.",
